Hardwick Simmons MBA: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 21, 2017 5:00 PM ET
Insurance

Company Overview of Prudential Capital and Investment Services, LLC



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Hardwick   Simmons MBAPresident, Prudential Capital and Investment Services, LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 7 Board Members in 7 different organizations across 12 different industries.See Board Relationships77--
Background

		Mr. Hardwick Simmons, also known as Wick, MBA, serves as President of Prudential Capital and Investment Services, LLC. Mr. Simmons joined The Nasdaq OMX Group, Inc. in February 2001 and served as its Chief Executive Officer from February 2001 to May 12, 2003. He served as the Unit President and Chairman of the Board at Lions Gate Entertainment Corp. He served as President of The Bond Club of New York, The. He began his career in the securities industry in 1966 when he ... served as a Financial Advisor at Hayden Stone, a predecessor firm of Shearson Lehman Brothers, Inc. He served as President of the Private Client Group at Shearson Lehman Brothers Inc. from 1983 to 1990. From May 1991 to January 2001, Mr. Simmons served as President and Chief Executive Officer of Prudential Securities Incorporated and President of its subsidiary, Prudential SGroup Inc. Since 1969, he served as Vice President, In Charge of Data Processing and Communications Division of Hayden sponsible for Retail Sales and Administration since 1973. He served as Senior Executive Vice President, overseeing Marketing and Sales for Shearson/American Express since 1977. He served in the U.S. Marine Corps Reserve from 1960 to 1966. He serves as the Chairman of The National Research Exchange Inc. He has been a Director of Geneva Acquisition Corp. since August 2006. Mr. Simmons has been an Independent Director of Lions Gate Entertainment Corp., since June 30, 2005. He serves as a Director of Invivoscribe Technologies, Inc. and National Academy Foundation. He serves as a Trustee of Groton School and Woods Hole Oceanographic Institution. He served as Chairman of Securities Industry and Financial Markets Association. He served as an Independent Non-Executive Director of Raymond James Financial, Inc from May 30, 2003 to February 18, 2016 and served as its Lead Director from 2006 to February 18, 2016. Mr. Simmons served as a Director of The Nasdaq OMX Group, Inc. from September 2001 to May 12, 2003. He served as a Director of The Partnership for New York City Inc. He served as a Director of Chicago Board Options Exchange Inc. and NYC2012 Inc. He serves as a Trustee of the Rippowam Cisqua School in Mt. Kisco, New York. He is a Member of Global Advisory Council at WTA Tour, Inc. He was the Chairman of the International Tennis Hall of Fame. He was a Member of the NASD Board of Governors since 2001. Mr. Simmons graduated from Harvard University with a BA in 1963 and received his M.B.A. from The Harvard Business School in 1966.Read Full Background




